{"cursor":"1230","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"The 'Auwers synthesis' is a series of organic reactions forming a flavonol from\na coumarone. This reaction was first reported by Karl von Auwers in 1908. K.\nv. Auwers et al. [[Chemische Berichte|Ber.]] '1908', 41, 4233. K. v.\nAuwers et al. [[Chemische Berichte|Ber.]] '1915', 48, 85. K. v. Auwers\net al. [[Chemische Berichte|Ber.]] '1916', 49, 809. K. v. Auwers, P.\nPohl, [[Ann.]] '1914', 405, 243.\n\n\n\nThe first step in this procedure is an acid catalyzed aldol condensation between\nbenzaldehyde and a 3-oxypentanone to an o-hydroxychalcone. Bromination of the\nalkene group gives a dibromo-adduct which rearranges to the flavonol by reaction\nwith potassium hydroxide.\n","linknr":106,"url":"Auwers_synthesis","recorded":1374541375,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Auwers_synthesis&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Auwers_synthesis&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Organic_reaction","/wiki/Flavonol","/wiki/Coumarone","/wiki/Karl_von_Auwers","#cite_note-1","#cite_note-2","#cite_note-3","#cite_note-4","/wiki/File:Auwers_synthesis.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Auwers_synthesis.png/500px-Auwers_synthesis